Package: xtop
Version: 0.46.3-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 37740
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 v0.46.3 hardens the resource guardian (now ON by default — sets
 XTOP_GUARD=0 to opt out), adds an App Load Distribution panel that
 shows per-app CPU/RAM/IO share with explicit percentages, and fixes
 the apps Manager being permanently disabled by registry budget
 enforcement when deep probes legitimately took >50ms (e.g. mongosh).
 .
 Other improvements: app detection now panic-safe (deferred snap
 assignment), trace mode for incident audit (xtop trace --once,
 --watch-confirmed), fast-pulse PSI sampling at 250ms, per-app
 behavioural baselines anchored on cgroup, multi-scale drift
 detection. Same two binaries as 0.46.2: xtop (full TUI) and
 xtop-agent (14MB lean fleet agent).
